main event: A civilian in Williams Bay, Wisconsin reported a 15-minute observation of a round object the size of a half dollar, with colors of red, white, yellow, and blue. The report lacked sufficient data for evaluation.
interesting points: The object was categorized as 'Civilian' with no conclusive evaluation due to insufficient data.
No photographs were included in the report.
The observation lasted for 15 minutes, indicating a prolonged sighting.
The object was described as having multiple colors, making it a distinct visual sighting.
The document was part of Project Blue Book, which was a US Air Force program for the investigation of UFO reports.
sighted object: round object, size of half dollar, with red, white, yellow, and blue colors
